race.comment: SASSIDORA (8) resumes for her second campaign having run a good race on debut at Cranbourne, showing speed and battling on well for third. Expect her to have improved over the break and she should get every chance bouncing out from the inside gate. IRREVERENT (6) resumes. She showed promise in three runs last time in behind some talented types who have gone on to better races. She should get every chance here. GET HONOR (3) is a well-bred filly by Savabeel on debut for the Walker yard. She's jumped out well and Damian Lane hops aboard which is a good sign. SATTVA (9) resumes. She was well beaten on debut at Ballarat but looks to have improved and can do much better. ALL TOO SINGLE (1) is going well and is in the mix again.
